    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-18T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="352"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3442: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Fortes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-18T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 18, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. I am reliably informed that three of the League Commission members leave
                    today returning to Asunción after having received <pb facs="0465" n="377"
                        xml:id="pg_377"/> agreement from Bolivia to integral arbitration. They
                    expect acceptance from President of Paraguay but difficulties with other
                    leaders.</p>
                <p>Above sent to Montevideo, Asunción.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
